# Server API conventions

## Module structure

Each API under `server/api/<name>/`:

```
index.js           # Express Router, auth guards, route wiring
*.controller.js    # Request handlers
*.model.js         # Sequelize model (if applicable)
*.integration.js   # Supertest integration tests
*.socket.js        # Socket.io handlers (optional)
```

## Route pattern

```javascript
router.get('/', auth.hasRole('admin'), controller.index);
router.get('/me', auth.isAuthenticated(), controller.me);
```

Match auth level of nearby routes in the same module.

## Controllers

- Use Sequelize promises (`.then/.catch`) consistent with existing code in the file
- Return appropriate HTTP status codes; use `res.status(401).end()` for auth failures
- Register new routers in `server/routes.js`

## Background jobs

Scheduled work lives in `server/app.js` and some controllers (METAR, TAF, roster, Firebase). Do not add new intervals or change timing without user approval.

## Real-time

Socket.io setup: `server/config/socketio.js`. JWT for sockets uses `socketio-jwt`. Follow existing event naming in `*.socket.js` / `*.events.js` files.
